  <body>
    <segment id="1">

Natural recapture</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="2" relname="reason">

The nature park that is being created between Jüterbog, Luckenwalde and Treuenbrietzen is still far too little known outside the region.</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="12" relname="span">  

It is therefore to be welcomed that Manfred Stolpe paid a visit to the extensive area the day before yesterday.</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="4" relname="background">  

An intended benefit of such official trips by the Prime Minister to the provinces is to draw as much public attention as possible to certain projects.</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="13" relname="span">

A circular route is to be created around the approximately 7000-hectare nature park.</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="18" relname="span">  

This would be a significant step towards the stated goal of developing the former military training area for tourism.</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="5" relname="evidence">

The hiking dune near Forst Zinna is already a popular excursion destination for locals and visitors alike.</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="17" relname="span">

This type of conversion - nature reclaims former military areas - is comparatively cheap.</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="7" relname="elaboration">  

However, the sections where dangerous ammunition may still be stored remain restricted areas.</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="16" relname="span">

Whether new jobs will be created in the long term by developing the conversion areas for tourism depends above all on how many curious visitors will come.</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="14" relname="preparation">

As was said :</segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="15" relname="span"> Stolpe was already there.</segment>
<group id="12" type="span" parent="18" relname="background" />
